'''Elizabeth Charnock''' (born 30 November 1966 in [[Philadelphia]], Pennsylvania) is a technologist and [[entrepreneur]]. Charnock is the author of [http://www.amazon.com/dp/0071629955 E-Habits: What You Must Do to Optimize Your Professional Digital Presence]. Charnock is currently CEO of Cataphora.
==References== * Elizabeth Charnock in [[GigaOM]], on [http://gigaom.com/cloud/do-we-need-a-line-between-big-data-and-big-brother/ Do we need a line between big data and big brother?] * Elizabeth Charnock in [[BusinessWeek]], on [http://www.businessweek.com/technology/content/may2011/tc20110516_162999.htm Why It's Hard to Replicate Silicon Valley's Successes Abroad] * Elizabeth Charnock in [[CNN]], on [http://edition.cnn.com/2010/TECH/web/08/25/digital.reflection/#fbid=g_HeIfZuAfy&wom=false Does your 'digital reflection' show your true self?] * Elizabeth Charnock in [[San Francisco Chronicle]], on [http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=/c/a/2010/04/17/BULL1CVCHK.DTL Meet the Boss: Elizabeth Charnock of Cataphora] * Elizabeth Charnock in [[The New York Times]], on [http://boss.blogs.nytimes.com/2010/08/17/bootstrapping-a-start-up-in-silicon-valley/ Bootstrapping a Start-Up in Silicon Valley] * Elizabeth Charnock in [[The New York Times]], on [http://www.nytimes.com/2011/08/11/business/smallbusiness/how-small-business-owners-are-coping-with-the-economic-turmoil.html?pagewanted=1&_r=1 Nervously Watching as the Economy Churns] * Elizabeth Charnock in [[The New York Times]], on [http://boss.blogs.nytimes.com/2011/02/16/can-you-start-a-tech-company-without-venture-capital/?src=busln Can You Start a Tech Company Without Venture Capital]
